The paper discusses the use of machine learning methods for predicting industrial aging processes, which falls under the category of predictive maintenance. The paper evaluates a range of data-driven models, including traditional stateless models and more complex recurrent neural networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of these models for predictive maintenance in an industrial setting also suggests that the paper may be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY) and control engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the use of neural networks in the paper suggests that it may also be categorized under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
